rereleased%20it%20in%20December%202023%2C%20and%20it%20immediately%20hit%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20bestseller%20list.%20Broadbent's%20career%20has%20been%20skyrocketing%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Broadbent%20is%20revisiting%20one%20of%20her%20earliest%20novels%20with%20Bramble%20at%20her%20side.%20Broadbent%20self-published%20%26quot%3BDaughter%20of%20No%20Worlds%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20installment%20of%20her%20%26quot%3BWar%20of%20Lost%20Hearts%26quot%3B%20series%20%E2%80%94%20in%202020%2C%20but%20it's%20getting%20a%20splashy%20new%20cover%20and%20release%20on%20October%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Business%20Insider%20ahead%20of%20the%20release%2C%20Broadbent%20reflected%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frebecca-ross-author-divine-rivals-book-publishing-advice-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eher%20publishing%20journey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20she%20loves%20working%20with%20a%20traditional%20publisher%2C%20Broadbent%20said%20there%20were%20big%20benefits%20to%20the%20self-publishing%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e72d7d6-cd83-4156-90d8-a3ba69359941%5C%22%3EMore%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBroadbent%20works%20with%20Bramble%20in%20a%20hybrid%20model%2C%20retaining%20some%20self-publishing%20rights%20for%20her%20e-books%20even%20as%20the%20publisher%20releases%20her%20novels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20people%20take%20me%20now%20being%20hybrid%20as%20some%20kind%20of%20a%20message%20that%20traditional%20publishing%20is%20'better'%20than%20self-publishing%2C%20and%20I%20do%20not%20find%20that%20to%20be%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Broadbent%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20get%20me%20wrong%2C%20I'm%20very%20happy%20with%20my%20partnership%20with%20my%20publisher%20because%20that%20was%20very%20specifically%20the%20right%20move%20for%20me.%20But%20as%20a%20net%2C%20I%20do%20not%20think%20that%20one%20is%20better.%20There%20are%20pluses%20and%20minuses%20to%20both%20routes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBroadbent%20said%20she%20initially%20self-published%20%26quot%3BDaughter%20of%20No%20Worlds%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20made%20her%20goal%20of%20writing%20full-time%20%26quot%3Bmore%20attainable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20went%20into%20self-publishing%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20one%20day%20becoming%20a%20full-time%20author%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20the%20research%20that%20I%20had%20done%20at%20the%20time%2C%20I%20had%20felt%20like%20that%20was%20a%20much%20more%20attainable%20goal%20through%20self-publishing%20than%20it%20was%20through%20traditional%20publishing%20because%20there's%20so%20much%20more%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20Broadbent%20was%20attracted%20to%20self-publishing%20because%20it%20can%20be%20lucrative%20quickly%2C%20which%20is%20a%20bonus%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20book%20deal%20or%20advance%20to%20offer%20financial%20support%20as%20you%20write.%20Some%20authors%20even%20make%20more%20money%20self-publishing%20than%20they%20would%20through%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falchemised-senlinyu-manacled-rewrite-plot-release-date-details-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etraditionally%20published%20book%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221665%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20cover%20of%20%26quot%3BDaughter%20of%20No%20Worlds%26quot%3B%20by%20Carissa%20Broadbent.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e7f46b1c1f80efbec54898%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222552%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BDaughter%20of%20No%20Worlds%26quot%3B%20by%20Carissa%20Broadbent.%3Cp%3ECarissa%20Broadbent%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20keep%20a%20much%20bigger%20piece%20of%20the%20pie%2C%26quot%3B%20Broadbent%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20authors%20self-publishing%20who%20are%20not%20household%20names%20by%20any%20means%20but%20who%20are%20making%20very%20comfortable%20middle-class%20livings%20doing%20this.%20So%20that%20was%20the%20route%20I%20took%20because%20I%20really%20thought%20I%20was%20never%20going%20to%20be%20a%20New%20York%20Times%20bestselling%20author%20anyway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20days%20of%20her%20career%2C%20Broadbent's%20novels%20were%20primarily%20e-books%2C%20and%20she%20said%20she%20started%20making%20money%20from%20them%20fairly%20quickly%20because%20she%20wasn't%20sharing%20that%20profit%20with%20a%20publisher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BE-books%20are%20very%2C%20very%2C%20very%20lucrative%20when%20you%20are%20self-published%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20keep%20everything%20essentially.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20overhead%20is%20so%20low%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20her%20books%20being%20available%20through%20the%20Kindle%20Unlimited%20program%20helped.%20%26quot%3BThose%20royalty%20structures%20for%20most%20traditional%20deals%20are%20not%20super%20advantageous%20to%20authors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a6b400db-d371-4004-af63-4c722f66fdf2%5C%22%3EWorking%20two%20jobs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESelf-publishing%20also%20suited%20Broadbent%20early%20in%20her%20career%20because%20she%20still%20worked%20a%20day%20job%20in%20marketing.%20She%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20fit%20writing%20into%20her%20life%2C%20and%20because%20she%20wasn't%20on%20a%20publisher's%20deadline%2C%20she%20could%20do%20it%20in%20the%20way%20that%20made%20sense%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Broadbent%2C%20that%20meant%20writing%20early%20in%20the%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20realized%20I%20was%20never%20going%20to%20write%20after%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20really%20stressful%20day%20job%2C%20and%20I%20worked%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20on%20the%20West%20Coast%2C%20so%20my%20days%20tended%20to%20bleed%20late.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBroadbent%20would%20get%20up%20around%204%3A30%20a.m.%20to%20write%20before%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Broadbent%20writes%20full-time%2C%20so%20she%20doesn't%20have%20to%20start%20as%20early%2C%20but%20that%20flexibility%20in%20the%20early%20years%20of%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frebecca-ross-rewrote-wild-reverence-before-publishing-divine-rivals-prequel-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewriting%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20a%20huge%20difference%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e63a3120-ef43-45f6-a6e8-2b69d2ed384b%5C%22%3EQuick%20turnaround%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20she%20didn't%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffourth-wing-tv-show-release-date-cast-streaming-details-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20book%20deal%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20she%20was%20exclusively%20self-publishing%2C%20Broadbent%20had%20an%20incentive%20to%20get%20her%20books%20up%20quickly%20so%20she%20could%20start%20making%20money.%20She%20said%20it%20was%20much%20simpler%20to%20actually%20publish%20when%20she%20was%20indie%2C%20even%20though%20she%20was%20still%20hiring%20editors%20to%20review%20her%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndie%20authors%20sometimes%20have%20a%20bad%20reputation%20for%20not%20editing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20books%20went%20through%20a%20lot%20of%20editing%20when%20I%20was%20indie%2C%20just%20as%20much%20as%20they%20go%20through%20now%2C%20honestly.%20But%20the%20difference%20is%20that%20I%20am%20the%20puppet%20master.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBroadbent%20said%20she%20could%20give%20editors%20with%20whom%20she%20had%20working%20relationships%20chunks%20of%20her%20books%20at%20a%20time%2C%20so%20she%20could%20continue%20drafting%20as%20they%20were%20being%20edited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20headshot%20of%20Carissa%20Broadbent.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e7f49acc993f9955cfe4db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarissa%20Broadbent.%3Cp%3ECarissa%20Broadbent%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20do%20things%20in%20parallel%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20flexibility%20to%20do%20that%20kind%20of%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20traditional%20publishing%2C%20we%20are%20mobilizing%20a%20giant%20machine%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%2C%20so%20that%20is%20not%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20much%20harder%20starts%20and%20stops%20to%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20book%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BCrowns%20of%20Nyaxia%26quot%3B%20series%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Lion%20and%20the%20Deathless%20Dark%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20scheduled%20for%20publication%20in%20August%202026%2C%20and%20Broadbent%20said%20she%20had%20to%20submit%20a%20complete%20first%20draft%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrom-blood-and-ash-series-order-jennifer-l-armentrout-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20novel%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20her%20editor%20about%20a%20year%20before%20that.%20She%20couldn't%20revise%20it%20until%20her%20editor%20had%20time%20with%20the%20book%2C%20so%20the%20process%20moved%20more%20slowly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20Broadbent%20said%20that%20you%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20physical%20process%20of%20printing%20books%20that%20comes%20with%20traditional%20publishing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20like%20over%20seven%20months%20just%20to%20physically%20produce%20the%20book%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20printing%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20copies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20her%20self-published%20e-books%2C%20the%20process%20was%20almost%20instantaneous%20for%20Broadbent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20basically%20press%20a%20button%2C%20and%2048%20hours%20later%2C%20there's%20the%20book%2C%26quot%